{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["Linux"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will fatal.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3NNC12ModelBuilderC","roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ModelBuilder"}],"role":"symbol","title":"ModelBuilder","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"NNC"}]},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModelBuilder"]},{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Confo